    <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-massert" content="The clip-path property takes the basic shape
    'circle' for clipping, with the 'closest-corner' size. There should be a full green circle.">
    <style><style><link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-massert">
    body {
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .test {
        position: absolute;
        left: 150px;
        top: 100px;
        width: 350px;
        height: 450px;
        background-color: red;
        clip-path: circle(closest-corner at 150px 200px);
    }

    .inner {
        position: absolute;
        top: -60px;
        left: -110px;
        width: circle(closest-corner at 150px 200px);
    }

    .inner {
        position: absolute;
        top: -60px;
        left: -110px;
        width: 520px;
        height: 520px;
        background-color: green;
    }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <p>The test passes if there is a full green circle.</p>
